<div id="Idea_3597"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3597-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3597">Federal Agencies Should Model Collaboration.&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/6834-4049">Lisa Blomgren Bingham</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">4 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">The Open Government Directive should help agencies model the practice of collaboration. This means that in deciding how to organize, expand, and institutionalize collaborative and participatory governance, agencies should consult broadly with their own staff. </div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3597" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3597', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2246&topicID=3597')">Comments (1)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3597"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2246">Between Federal Agencies</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3597"></div>
